{
  "texts": [
    "It emphasizes that the pursuit of model performance alone, while neglecting human factors, is something that needs attention.",
    "This section concisely overviews prominent mathematical problem types and associated datasets, spanning ARITHMETIC, MATH WORD PROB-LEMS, GEOMETRY, AUTOMATED THEOREM PROVING, and MATH IN VISION CONTEXT.",
    "This category of problems entails pure mathematical operations and numerical manipulation, devoid of the need for the model to interpret text, images, or other contextual elements.",
    "An illustrative example is presented below, where \"Q\" denotes questions and \"A\" for answers.",
    "The dataset MATH-140 (Yuan et al., 2023) contains 401 arithmetic expressions for 17 groups."
  ]
}